author: @andrewjones54
text: I've noticed the input shape for your models is [None, width, height, 1] (i.e. you're using width before height, the same as cv2), but the tflearn documentation (http://tflearn.org/layers/conv/#convolution-2d) seems to specify that the inputs are [batch, height, width, in_channels] (height before width).  I've built my models in Keras and this is the same there...  Could you possibly be squishing your input images into a portrait shape rather than landscape?
